      <div style="max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;">

        <!-- 5. Quick-Answer box (AEO / Position 0) -->
        <div id="quick" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-6">
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-stone-200 bg-white" style="box-shadow:0 10px 40px rgba(60,30,10,0.08);">
            <div class="px-6 py-5 sm:px-8" style="background:#2D6A4F">
              <p class="font-sora text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] mb-1.5" style="color:#ffd6c9">The short answer</p>
              <h2 class="font-lora font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl leading-snug" style="color:#faf7f4">How Well Do African Greys Really Talk?</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6 sm:p-8">
              <p class="font-sora text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">African Greys are the best-talking parrots in the world. A well-socialised Grey can learn anywhere from a few dozen to <strong>200–1,000+ words</strong>, usually says its first word around <strong>12–18 months</strong>, and — uniquely — uses words <strong>in context</strong> rather than just mimicking. No breeder can guarantee a talker, but a Grey raised with daily conversation has the best odds of any companion bird.</p>
