        <!-- 13. Trust band + birds -->
        <h2 class={h2}>What Do You Really Get From a Breeder Who Raises Talkers?</h2>
        <p class={p}>You can't buy a guaranteed talker, but you can buy the best possible odds — and that starts with how the bird was raised. Here at C.A.Gs, every African Grey leaves fully weaned and socialised, talked to daily since weaning, with <a href="/blog/african-grey-parrot-price-what-you-get/" class={lnk} style="color:#b04228">PCR DNA sexing, an avian-vet health certificate, and CITES Appendix I paperwork</a> — all captive-bred in the USA and fully documented.</p>
        <figure class="my-6">
          <img src="/jins-jeni-congo-african-grey-pair-talking-birds.webp" srcset="/jins-jeni-congo-african-grey-pair-talking-birds-480.webp 480w, /jins-jeni-congo-african-grey-pair-talking-birds.webp 640w" sizes="(min-width: 768px) 640px, 92vw" width="640" height="480" alt="Jins and Jeni, a hand-raised Congo African Grey pair, socialised with daily speech at the C.A.Gs aviary" title="Jins & Jeni — a hand-raised Congo African Grey talking pair | C.A.Gs" class="w-full rounded-2xl border border-stone-200" loading="lazy" />
          <span class={figc}>Jins &amp; Jeni — raised inside the conversation, like every C.A.Gs chick.</span>
        </figure>
